Problem Statement

Your school is building a digital system to track student performance. Each student has:

A roll number
A name
Marks in 4 subjects:
Math
Science
English
Computer
All marks must be stored neatly using nested structures.

Your job is to read the details of N students, calculate each student’s total marks, and finally print the details of the student who scored the highest total marks.

Input Format

1) First line: Number of students (N)

2) For each student, enter 6 lines:

Roll number
Name (no spaces)
Math marks
Science marks
English marks
Computer marks
Constraints

1 ≤ N ≤ 100
Roll number > 0
Marks: 0 to 100
If two or more students tie, print the one who appears last.
Output Format

Print the topper’s details in below format:

Topper Details:
Roll No: roll_here
Name: name_here
Total Marks: total_here
Sample Input 0

2
101
Rohan
80
70
75
85
102
Meena
90
85
88
92
Sample Output 0

Topper Details:
Roll No: 102
Name: Meena
Total Marks: 355









#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

struct Marks {
    int math;
    int science;
    int english;
    int computer;
};

struct Student {
    int roll;
    char name[50];
    struct Marks m;
    int total;
};

int main() {
    int n, i, topper = 0;
    struct Student s[100];

    scanf("%d", &n);

    for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        scanf("%d", &s[i].roll);
        scanf("%s", s[i].name);
        scanf("%d", &s[i].m.math);
        scanf("%d", &s[i].m.science);
        scanf("%d", &s[i].m.english);
        scanf("%d", &s[i].m.computer);

        s[i].total = s[i].m.math + s[i].m.science +
                     s[i].m.english + s[i].m.computer;

        if (s[i].total >= s[topper].total) {
            topper = i;
        }
    }

    printf("Topper Details:\n");
    printf("Roll No: %d\n", s[topper].roll);
    printf("Name: %s\n", s[topper].name);
    printf("Total Marks: %d\n", s[topper].total);
  
    return 0;
}
